Interface TreeNode<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    TreeNodeImpl

    public interface TreeNode<T>
    Tree where each node can have a name, properties and an associated object.

      • getChild

        TreeNode<T> getChild(String name)
        Find a child node by name. The name may contain '/' to delimit names to find a child more then one level deep. To find a node named 'bar' that is a child of a child named 'foo', use the name 'foo/bar'.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the child. May contain the '/' path separator.
        Returns:
        the requested node or null if the child was not found
